-- Kyocera, KDDI, IHI to Build $345 Million 70-Megawatt Solar Plant
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2012-07-31T07:22:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-31/kyocera-kddi-ihi-to-build-345-million-70-megawatt-solar-plant.html
Kyocera Corp. (6971) , a Japanese solar-
panel maker, formed a joint venture with partners including  KDDI
Corp. (9433)  and  IHI Corp. (7013)  to build a 27 billion yen ($345 million) 70-
megawatt power plant in the south of the country.  Mizuho Corporate Bank Ltd. will help arrange loans for the
solar plant, Kyocera said today in a statement.  They will begin construction in September and finish by the
autumn of 2013, Kyocera said. The partners also include  Kyudenko
Corp. (1959) , Takenaka Corp.,  Bank of Kyoto Ltd. (8369)  and  Kagoshima Bank
Ltd. (8390)  Kyocera announced an initial agreement in April.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in Tokyo at 
